CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 14, 1959 reads: "Wall collapses - The eastern wall of Grob's Tavern at 2150 Wylie Ave. collapsed about 4:30 P.M. Tuesday, but nobody was injured. Maurice Grob the owner says fire which destroyed the next door building in November, left the Grob structure without support on that side of the building. No estimate was placed on the damage, but the tavern is not operating. Patrolman Johnny Daniels is shown doing guard duty, while an unidentified spectator looks on." --Harris Photo.
TitMainTitle: Exterior of Grob's Tavern with collapsed wall, seen from across street, with Pittsburgh Department of Public Works sawhorses, police officer Johnny Daniels, and woman in foreground, 2150 Wylie Avenue, Hill District
